body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for contacting our customer support. My name is Joshua Cooper, and I represent Cooper Motors. May I have your name please?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Hi, my name is Julie Martinez.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Julie. To assist you better, could you provide me with your date of birth in the format day, month, year?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, it's two eight zero six nineteen eighty-nine.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you. Next, could you please provide me with the first five digits of your home phone number?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Yes, it's eight seven eight two five.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Julie. Your cooperation is appreciated. Is there anything else I can assist you with today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: No, that's all for now, thank you.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for reaching out, Julie. If you have any further questions, feel free to contact us. Have a great day!
